    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>When the Children Spend Hours Online</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Christy Gavitt letter holds a harmful outcome of long hours spent in front of computer is epidemic of overweight children and adolescents</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Family's Choices Can Blunt the Effect of Video Violence'' (front page, Sept. 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Family's Choices Can Blunt the Effect of Video Violence'' (front page, Sept. 25):</p>
        <p>Another harmful outcome of long hours spent in front of the computer is the epidemic of overweight children and adolescents, something rarely seen before the personal computer age. An overweight child will have serious difficulty in keeping his weight within normal levels as an adult. The skyrocketing public health costs associated with ailments related to obesity may have long-term effects on our society.</p>
        <p>Perhaps parents should not only observe their children's computer activities but also regularly tell them to turn off the machine, go outside and get some exercise.</p>
        <p>CHRISTY GAVITT  Segou, Mali, Sept. 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
